text: Unemployment rates in November ranged from 2.2% in UT to 4.9% in NV.
Real GDP growth between Q3 2021 and Q3 2022 ranged from -2.2% in Louisiana to 5.7% in Idaho.
November state average private weekly earnings ranged from $856 in MS to $1,345 in MA.
Real retail GDP in Q3 2022 was higher than in Q3 2021 in 32 states.
Between Q3 2021 and Q3 2022, house prices increased at least 7% in each of the 50 states.
Nevada saw its highest real manufacturing GDP since 2005 in Q3 2022.
Leisure and hospitality jobs in November 2022 were above November 2019 levels in 16 states.
In November 2022, DC saw its lowest unemployment rate in over 45 years.
Manufacturing jobs in November 2022 were above November 2019 levels in 27 states.
Q3 2022 was the first quarter since 2017 that ID’s annual house price growth was under 10%.
